                    "name": "What is an Operating System?",
                    "content": {
                        "explanation": "An Operating System (OS) is system software that manages computer hardware and software resources. Popular operating systems include Windows, macOS, and Linux. The OS provides a user interface and manages files, programs, and devices."
                    },
